## üîç **Duplicate Component Analysis Summary**

### **1. FILTER COMPONENTS ‚Äî HIGH PRIORITY (~500 lines of duplication)**

| Component | Lines | Pattern |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| `equipment-filters.tsx` | 100 | Search + Status + Reset |
| `user-filters.tsx` | 98 | Search + Role + Reset |
| `location-filters.tsx` | 78 | Search + Reset |
| `vendor-filters.tsx` | 76 | Search + Reset |
| `parts-filters.tsx` | 108 | Search + Category + Reset |
| `work-order-filters.tsx` | 143 | Search + Status + Priority + Date + Reset |

**Identical patterns across ALL 6 components:**
- Container wrapper styling (100% identical CSS)
- Search input styling (100% identical CSS)
- Search icon positioning and animation
- Clear (X) button styling and behavior
- Reset All button styling
- `handleSearchSubmit` logic (95% identical)
- `hasActiveFilters` calculation pattern

**Recommended Fix:** Create a generic `FilterBar` component:
```tsx
<FilterBar
  basePath="/assets/equipment"
  searchPlaceholder="SEARCH BY NAME OR SERIAL..."
  filters={[
    { name: "status", options: statusOptions }
  ]}
  searchParams={searchParams}
/>
```
